CAN BE REALIZED. ONE APPROACH WHICH MAY BE USED IS TO
PURCHASE THE PROPERTY IF THE TOTAL RENT RECEIPTS EXCEED TOTAL
EXPENSES. THESE EXPENSES CONSIST OF PROPERTY TAXES, INSURANCE,
MORTGAGE PAYMENTS, MAINTENANCE COSTS, AND OTHER MISC. COSTS.
IN THE MODEL TO BE USED IN THIS PROGRAM RENTAL INCOME IS KNOWN.
ALL EXPENSES ARE KNOWN EXCEPT THE MONTHLY MORTGAGE PAYMENT.
